  "body": "Copying the validator registry on every EpochContext data access outside the chain module is not sustainable.\r\n\r\nSolution TBD\r\n\r\nSee https://discordapp.com/channels/593655374469660673/593655641445367808/722918727137493011\r\nfrom the chat:\r\n> You can return a read-only interface, and avoid that encapsulation problem\r\n[4:04 PM]\r\nAnd then just maintain a single dictionary that you never copy\r\n[4:05 PM]\r\nAnd then you have two options: either special-case when eth1 has a deep-reorg and we have much bigger things to worry about (lighthouse), or do a layered approach, where you wrap the old dictionary, and only use the common part that is still the same between deep reorgs (zrnt).\r\n[4:06 PM]\r\nIt saves you a lot of time and allocations to not copy the full registry all the time (the registry is mostly pubkey data)",
